org.eng.aisp

Class SensorRecording<WINDOW extends IDataWindow<double[]>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.util.TaggedEntity
      • org.eng.aisp.SensorRecording<WINDOW>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>, ITaggedEntity

    public class SensorRecording<WINDOW extends IDataWindow<double[]>>
extends TaggedEntity
implements ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>
    Represents the combination of a sensor, a data window together with associated training labels. The recording may be classified as either a sample or a baseline. Baselines are recordings used to characterize a situation or condition, for example, normal operation. Samples are generally compared against a set of baselines. A recording may have features extracted and attached to it.
    Author:
    dawood
